-- Colombian Stock Movers: Grupo Nutresa, Ecopetrol Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-03-26T20:26:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/colombian-stock-movers-grupo-nutresa-ecopetrol-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 1 percent to 15,109.53, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.9 percent to 1,747.80.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA)  (NUTRESA CB) decreased 0.3 percent to
21,500 pesos, after earlier dropping as much as 0.9 percent. The
target price for  Colombia ’s biggest food producer was cut to
26,000 pesos from 27,000 pesos by analysts including Pedro Herrera at HSBC Holdings Plc in a research report today, citing
a drop in the value of Nutresa’s stake in related companies.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
gained 1.7 percent to 5,450 pesos. Ecopetrol reached a record
high on a closing basis as investors buy shares ahead of the
company’s “very attractive” dividend payment to minority
shareholders starting April 25, Juan David Pineros, an analyst
at brokerage Interbolsa SA, said in a telephone interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
